newsitem.title: SINGAPORE: Singapore oil products mixed, gas oil rangebound.
newsitem.headline: Singapore oil products mixed, gas oil rangebound.

text.p: Singapore oil products were mixed on Friday with gas oil remaining rangebound despite the steep losses on London's gas oil market, while naphtha slipped on lower crudes, traders said.

They said gas oil swaps slipped earlier in the day to trade at $27.75 per barrel, but recovered to Thursday's level on talk of emerging Chinese buying interest. Traders said China recently bought around 30,000 tonnes of first half October gas oil at under $220 per tonne c+f and was bidding at $215. A bid for mid-October gas oil was seen at $27.85, with an offer from a major seen at $28.15 for Oct 18-22, down from Thursday's $27.85.

Jet fuel continued to be under supply pressure with two S.Korean refiners heard offering October barrels at 60-70 a barrel over Sigapore quotes fob. A Korean refiner recently sold a cargo to a Japanese buyers at $1.75 a barrel premium c+f. Physical jet fuel was offered lower for October 11-16 to $29.30 down 20 cents from Thursday. Another offer was seen for a later date at $29.50.

Nepal was close to awarding its October kerosene import tender to IPG at $245 a tonne c+f, but cancelled it due to technical problems, source said. Nepal will reissue the tender next week to seek one-two November cargoes.

Naphtha fell slightly in line with lower crude values and a weaker swaps market. October swaps were quoted at $21.10/21.40, down from Thursday's close of $21.30-21.55. Gasoline was unchanged but sentiments were bullish on expectations of tightening supplies as the export-oriented Balongan, Indonesia, crude unit and cracker go down for maintenance from October 1. The 125,000-bpd crude unit down for 24-days and 80,000-bpd residue catalytic cracker down for 60-days. In Singapore, bid for 95-octane was unchanged from Thursday at $22.90 per barrel fob. Fuel oil prices remained directionless and was stuck in a $115-$118 range.--Singapore Newsroom (+65-870 3084)
